<h2 class="bold font-l">"That was pretty sick man..."</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Despite being a movie about monsters, Hotel Transylvania is a pretty lighthearted film with the monsters featured mostly humanized. So it comes as a shock in-universe and out when Wayne the Werewolf has his instincts kick in when dealing with a certain obstacle in the road. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedyBurst" class='trope-example-link'>Black Comedy Burst</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="3n2v7g" data-video-descrip="Dracula is not impressed, with how a certain in-flight movie is representing vampires." data-video-title="Twilight" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/3n2v7g_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/3n2v7g.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/TakeThat" data-video-tropename="Take That!" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/HotelTransylvania" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/3n2v7g.jpg">
